SHANGHAI - Rafael Nadal underlined his status as world number one and the man to beat at the Shanghai Masters as he powered into the quarter-finals at the expense of Fabio Fognini on Thursday. READ: Nadal races into Shanghai third round The 31-year-old Spaniard was comfortable in seeing off the 28th-ranked Italian 6-3, 6-1 and will play sixth seed Grigor Dimitrov in the last eight. Top seed Nadal is chasing a seventh title this season, but a career-first Shanghai Masters. AFP